<paragraph blockId="10.[822,1446,1299,1358]" box="[1094,1174,1331,1358]" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">
(
<figureCitation box="[1103,1165,1331,1358]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,863,880]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,820]" captionTargetId="figure-501@10.[132,1455,215,820]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 5. — Scanning electron micrographs of hybodont shark teeth from Angeac-Charente:A, B, lateral tooth of Parvodus celsucuspus Rees, Cuny, Pouech &amp; Mazin, 2013 (ANG M-107) in labial (A) and occlusal (B) views; C, anterior tooth of Parvodus celsucuspus (ANG M-17) in labial view; D, dermal denticle (ANG M-109) in lateral view; E, F, dermal denticle (ANG M-108) in lateral (E) and apical (F) views. Scale bar: C, 1 mm; A, B, D-F, 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902045/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[812,1456,1396,1581]" box="[813,957,1396,1422]" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">
<collectionCode box="[813,957,1396,1422]" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">DESCRIPTION</collectionCode>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[812,1456,1396,1581]" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">
This species is characterized by high-cusped anterior teeth, and is well represented at Angeac-Charente.The material includes numerous isolated teeth and dermal denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1279,1491,1518]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,863,880]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,820]" captionTargetId="figure-501@10.[132,1455,215,820]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 5. — Scanning electron micrographs of hybodont shark teeth from Angeac-Charente:A, B, lateral tooth of Parvodus celsucuspus Rees, Cuny, Pouech &amp; Mazin, 2013 (ANG M-107) in labial (A) and occlusal (B) views; C, anterior tooth of Parvodus celsucuspus (ANG M-17) in labial view; D, dermal denticle (ANG M-109) in lateral view; E, F, dermal denticle (ANG M-108) in lateral (E) and apical (F) views. Scale bar: C, 1 mm; A, B, D-F, 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902045/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), as well as a few incomplete cephalic and dorsal fin spines(
<bibRefCitation author="Neraudeau" box="[1225,1440,1523,1549]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Neraudeau" pageId="10" pageNumber="691" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref44595" refString="NERAUDEAU D., ALLAIN R., BALLEVRE M., BATTEN D. J., BUFFE- TAUT E., COLIN J. P., DABARD M. P., DAVIERO- GOMEZ V., EL ALBANI A., GOMEZ B., GROSHENY D., LE LoeUFF J., LEPRINCE A., MARTIN- CLOSAS C., MASURE E., MAZIN J. - M., PHILIPPE M., POUECH J., TONG H., TOURNEPICHE J. - F. &amp; VULLO R. 2012. - The Hauterivian-Barremian lignitic bone bed of Angeac (Charente, SW France): stratigraphical, palaeobiological and palaeogeographical implications. Cretaceous Research 37: 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2012.01.006" type="journal article" year="2012">
Néraudeau 
<emphasis box="[1339,1385,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
), that are identical to those of Cherves-de-Cognac (
<bibRefCitation author="REES J. &amp; CUNY G. &amp; POUECH J. &amp; MAZIN J. M." box="[1291,1440,1554,1581]" journalOrPublisher="Cretaceous Research" pageId="10" pageNumber="691" pagination="122 - 131" part="44" refId="ref47784" refString="REES J., CUNY G., POUECH J. &amp; MAZIN J. M. 2013. - Non-marine selachians from the basal Cretaceous of Charente, SW France. Cretaceous Research 44: 122 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.04.002" title="Non-marine selachians from the basal Cretaceous of Charente, SW France" type="journal article" year="2013">
Rees 
<emphasis box="[1340,1386,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="691">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
